{Baker Partnership-StaymanTransfers 19}
{[show NS]
Even with a 6-card \S suit SOUTH uses Stayman because he also has a 4-card 
\H suit. Given a choice, playing a 4-4 Major fit is usually 
preferable to a 6-2 or even a 6-3 fit.
 

 
But here NORTH doesn't have four \Hs so SOUTH just bids 
the game where he knows the partnership holds eight trumps.}


